    <note>Liang(1) Zimei [1142] Shi's [1137] grandson, Su(1) Ce's [1507] maternal grandfather. Two presumed cousins, Zibo [3560], Ziting [3562] and documented cousin, Zishu [3561] all held office as fiscal intendants during the same period (circuit not designated in SHY:ZG, 68.16b-17a). Another presumed cousin, Ziya [3563], was Xia(2) Anqi's [698] son-in-law. Liang(1) Yu [3566], the son-in-law of Diao(1) Zhan's [1634] nephew and Liang(1) Duan [1140] had the same generational name as his grandsons and grandnephews. Zimei was the maternal grandfather of Su(1) Ze [1507], who used his yin to enter the civil service. XCBSB, 13.8a, 25.13a-13b, 23b; SHY:ZG, 43.6b-7a, 68.17a; Wang Anzhong, WJ, 8.9a. CBD, 3, 1059.</note>
